Iavan Pijoos, News24(File, Nielen de Klerk, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria - A 2-year-old-girl is&nbsp;suffering second degree burns to her body after a pot of boiling water spilled onto her at her home in Cullinan, near Pretoria, on Thursday, paramedics said.&nbsp;Paramedics were called to a local clinic in the area, where the child&nbsp;had been&nbsp;taken. The child was in a serious condition, Netcare 911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe said.An Emergency Care Practitioner managed to stabilise the child before she was transported to a hospital in Pretoria.This incident happened at 15:00 on Thursday afternoon.&nbsp;Netcare 911 advised all parents and child minders to keep a close watch on children when they are around water - whether the water&nbsp;was in a bathtub, a wading pool, a fish pond, a swimming pool, or in a pot on a stove. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.